result.execSummary:
On one or more charges, the deferred prosecution or sentencing agreement(s) on this case were fulfilled, and the charge(s) were dismissed.

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt: 2:19 pm case called. Defendant Devan D. Buckholt in court.  Steven Paul Anderson appeared for the State of Wisconsin.   Right to Counsel discussed. Court accepts waiver of counsel. Defendant advised of minimum/maximum penalty.  Plea colloquy entertained.  Collateral consequences explained.  Consequences explained for failure to abide by terms of PPDA. Chapter 950 compliance addressed.  Plea: No Contest to Count 1.  Court accepts plea and stays JOC. Court dismisses and reads-in.   Court accepts terms and conditions of PPDA.  Matter stayed for 12 months. Court reminds defendant regarding bond and potential charges for violations.

Complete ID process with the Sheriff's Department.  Defendant not to be in possession of any dangerous weapons capable of causing harm.  The defendant must maintain absolute sobriety, may not be present upon the premises of any bars, and is prohibited from possessing/ingesting any impairing substances that have not been prescribed by a physician.

Case Called @ 1:47 PM: Defendant Devan D. Buckholt in court.  Steven Paul Anderson appeared for the State of Wisconsin.   Complaint Stated - Advised of offense and minimum/maximum penalty.  ADA serves Complaint - Receipt Admitted - Reading Waived.  Advised of right of Counsel.  Def does not wish counsel today.  NGP received and entered as to both charges.   Def referred to SPD for eligibility process - to meet with SPD today.  STC Scheduled - NOH Given.  Court enters Riverside Ruling in favor of the State and probable cause finding as to each count alleged within the complaint.  Status conference scheduled for June 23, 2015 at 09:30 am.
